{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Include benefit income in Child Maintenance calculations",
        "additional_details": "Currently, a working parent earning around \u00a32,000 per month may pay about \u00a3240 per child, per month while a parent receiving a similar amount through benefits pays only a flat rate of around \u00a37 per week. This creates unfairness and reduces the financial support children receive.\r\n\r\nThe cost of raising a child does not change based on where a parent\u2019s income comes from. CMS calculations should reflect the full financial position of both parents to ensure fairness and better support for children.",
        "background": "We call on the Government to reform Child Maintenance Service (CMS) rules so payments are based on a parent\u2019s total income, including benefits, not just earnings.",
